news.title: Mangaluru civic body says no extension of offline property tax payment system
news.para: In a memorandum to MCC commissioner Akshy Sridhar, KCCI president Shashidhar Pai Maroor stated that the MCC’s online portal for payment of property tax has some teething issues.

news.title: Nashik: City survey office starts ownership confirmation and inquiry work
news.para: According to Kishorchandra Deore, special deputy superintendent of land records, the work of preparing the maps of properties in extended areas of the Nashik Municipal Corporation has been completed.

news.title: More property tax defaulters in Ludhiana get notices
news.para: The officials claimed that serving notices is helping them in the recovery process. In the past few days, they have received Rs 1 crore in pending dues from the defaulters.

news.title: Panchkula: Environment clearance to Amravati Enclave housing project withdrawn
news.para: The SEIAA has also found that the project proponent has constructed two wings of a building on green belt in violation of the norms.

news.title: DCBL launches app for cement sale, picks Nagpur for pilot project
news.para: Executive director of DBCL Hakimuddin Ali said the app targets retail consumers who need cement enough to build a 5,000 square feet property.

news.title: CPCB panel recommends Rs 76 crore penalty on seven Sonipat builders
news.para: The report claims that these builders violated not only the environmental rules but also the licence terms and conditions. The district town planner’s office had given them only partial completion certificates.

news.title: DTCP, admin holding up IIT audit: Chintels Paradiso residents
news.para: Citing an interim report submitted by the IIT, the residents said neither the Gurgaon administration nor the town and country planning department had chosen an agency to conduct a lab testing of the debris.

news.title: DHFL scam: Dheeraj Wadhawan may have to face personal insolvency action
news.para: Experts said that Dheeraj Wadhawan's likely insolvency would be among the handful of high-profile personal bankruptcy cases, such as that against Anil Ambani, to reach the NCLT.

news.title: Investigate Jaiprakash Associates: SAIL to NCLT
news.para: According to sources familiar with the contents of the lawsuit, SAIL has accused Jaiprakash Associates of pledging shares of Bhilai Jaypee Cement without its authorisation to Yes Bank for loans that were obtained by other Jaypee Group companies.

news.title: INOX's Siddharth Jain buys luxury quadruplex in Mumbai for Rs 144 crore
news.para: At Rs 1.36 lakh per sq ft the deal enters the tally of costliest houses in India. The amalgamated apartment in Raheja Legend is spread across 10,567-sq-ft on 42nd, 43rd, 44th and 46th floor. Jain has bought the apartment as a legal guardian of his three minor daughters, showed the registered agreement.

news.title: Won't conduct structural audits of five high-rises, says IIT-Roorkee
news.para: In February, the department of town and country planning wrote to the premier engineering institute for conducting an audit of the structural strength of the projects — Raheja Vedanta in Sector 108, Raheja Atharva in Sector 109, Brisk Lumbini in Sector 109, M3M Woodshire in Sector 107 and Mahindra Aurai in Sector 110A — in the wake of the Chintels Paradiso housing society tragedy.

news.title: Steel companies withholding rates, supply also not enough: Builders
news.para: ​Procuring steel has also become difficult. This is expected to have a major impact on the infrastructure sector as it uses the equipment. Shortage of construction equipment can slow down infrastructure work, he said.

news.title: Holcim Group considers sale of Indian arms Ambuja Cement, ACC
news.para: Holcim is believed to have held early-stage negotiations with JSW and Adani Group, among others, to explore their interest levels. Both are recent entrants in the cement sector but have aggressive plans to ramp up.

news.title: Only 917 of 9,700 illegal constructions demolished in Nagpur, HC told
news.para: The affidavit was submitted in PILs by Ajay Tiwari through counsel M Anil Kumar contending that the respondents granted approval for construction of houses but failed to act against them for carrying out illegal constructions and non-sanctioned alterations like misusing basement space reserved for parking for another purpose.

news.title: Malls plan rent hikes hearing cash counters ring at stores
news.para: Several retailers saved nearly 20% of their annual lease during the last two years due to rent concessions, which helped curtail net losses. However, over the past few months, retail sales have outpaced the pre-Covid levels, triggering a fresh round of negotiations, companies said.
